## Step One - Nonuniform padding using `PadNumX` Function   




### Explanation :     This functions calculates pads per side based on kernel size 'ks' aiming at non uniform paddings like (a+b)-symmetrical ones commonly encountered when dealing symmetric group convolution architectures such VGGish networks.





---







 ##Step Two – Activating Group Convolution With Squeeze Operators






 ###Explanation :~ Here, squeeze operators (`SELN`) replace conventional batch normalization layers after every convolutional layer except those followed directly After identity skip connections.(Squeeze operator replaces Batch Normalization). These modified convolutions enforce tighter coupling between feature maps leading improved performance while simplifying network structure compared traditional BN implementation which often requires meticulous hyperparameter tuning due its sensitivity nature.<br> <p/> In addition To squeezing operations being computationally efficient they introduce sparsity into activation patterns thereby facilitating gradient flow during backpropagation enhancing overall optimization process.</P><BR>.<Br />

