## Layers & Operators   




* **Padding**: Instead using `padding` parameter explicitly during layer construction (`PaddedConv`), exploit implicit padding offered via zero-padded convolution achieved simply changing stride from'stride=' instead setting it equal half integer value than desired dilation factor ('dilations'). This eliminates redundant calculations associated explicit paddings while maintaining intended spacing between features extracted at different scales across channels due dilated convolutions. For instance replacing "conv" line reads -     ``w, h -> Conv(...) ``` With `` w // d + H := DilatedConvolution(... )```` Where `/()` denotes ceiling operation ensuring integral number division resulting into exact feature map dimensions matching target output size after applying fractional strides induced dilations..






This optimization introduces a subtle change but significantly improves computational efficiency without compromising accuracy since both approaches achieve identical results albeit employing distinct mechanisms behind closed hood abstraction provided courtesy PyTorch implementation details exposed publicly alongside documentation pertaining model architectures like ResNet et al.,.

